-[song ends]
-[doorbell chiming]

41:00.001 --> 41:02.045
[sinister instrumental
music playing]

41:05.423 --> 41:07.842
Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit! Shit!

41:07.926 --> 41:09.135
Okay, what's the plan?

41:09.219 --> 41:10.428
I can't believe
she's actually here.

41:10.512 --> 41:12.389
Well, of course
she's fucking here.

41:12.514 --> 41:14.099
-[Dorothy]
I told you she'd come.
-[Vic] There's no time.

41:14.182 --> 41:15.475
Okay. What are we gonna do?

41:15.558 --> 41:17.686
-[Casey] Drown her.
-[Jane] Poison her.

41:17.769 --> 41:20.021
-Turn her into boron.
-Turn the lights out
and pretend we're not home.

41:20.146 --> 41:21.690
Who wants deviled eggs?

41:21.773 --> 41:23.983
-Hit her over the head
with some ham.
-Poison her.

41:24.067 --> 41:25.944
-[Jane] But with ham, yes.
Poison her with ham.
-[all squabbling indistinctly]

41:26.027 --> 41:28.071
-Give her so much ham,
she explodes.
-Okay, no more bullshit!

41:28.863 --> 41:30.365
Isabel is here.

41:30.490 --> 41:33.702
Where do you stand? Stay or go.

41:33.785 --> 41:35.120
-Stay!
-Go!

41:35.203 --> 41:36.830
[Madame Rouge] Okay.
And I'm a go.

41:36.913 --> 41:40.917
All right. That was slightly
less unified than I'd expected.

41:41.042 --> 41:43.461
[doorbell chiming]

41:49.384 --> 41:50.260
Wait!

41:52.637 --> 41:55.557
We all know
we're in some sort
of fabricated existence here,

41:55.640 --> 41:57.559
whether we want
to stay or leave.

41:57.684 --> 42:01.062
Whatever our differences,
there is an almighty god
at our front door.

42:01.187 --> 42:02.814
A spiteful god
who didn't think twice

42:02.897 --> 42:05.400
of turning her most ardent
worshippers into dust.

42:05.525 --> 42:06.776
So, let's just take a breath.

42:06.901 --> 42:09.404
[Cliff inhales deeply]

42:10.113 --> 42:11.573
She said...

42:11.656 --> 42:13.742
All we need to do
is get through dinner.

42:13.867 --> 42:17.996
So, just shut your pie holes
and put on a happy face. Hmm?

42:21.833 --> 42:22.959
Hmm?

42:24.044 --> 42:25.295
[Dorothy sighs]

42:28.423 --> 42:33.970
[in sing-song voice]
Hello! I'm here!
Where's my ham?

42:34.095 --> 42:35.555
[chuckles]

42:37.140 --> 42:40.018
Oh! I didn't know
there was a theme.

42:45.565 --> 42:50.445
My goodness,
this all looks divine!

42:52.947 --> 42:54.032
Sit.

42:55.116 --> 42:55.950
[energy pulsing]

42:56.034 --> 42:57.952
Now, let's see.

42:58.078 --> 42:59.496
Shall we start the festivities

42:59.621 --> 43:02.457
with a little
Immortimas spirit?

43:02.540 --> 43:04.209
How about
we go around the table

43:04.292 --> 43:07.337
and share what
we're all grateful for? Hmm?

43:09.005 --> 43:10.131
I'll go first.

43:10.882 --> 43:15.053
I'm grateful for... me.

43:15.136 --> 43:17.847
[laughs] Oh, this is fun.

43:17.972 --> 43:19.182
[continues laughing]

43:19.307 --> 43:20.642
Who's next?

43:20.725 --> 43:22.018
Mister Mummy Man?

43:22.811 --> 43:24.312
[Larry] Uh...

43:24.437 --> 43:28.483
Well, um, I guess I'm grateful
to be here with my family,

43:28.566 --> 43:30.485
and to introduce them all
to my boyfriend.

43:31.861 --> 43:34.239
How sweet. And?

43:35.573 --> 43:38.243
-And... and for the--
-[clattering]

43:38.326 --> 43:40.662
The pleasure
of worshipping you, Isabel.

43:40.787 --> 43:43.081
-[in demonic voice] Immortus!
-[thunder rumbling]

43:44.165 --> 43:46.334
[malicious music playing]

43:51.047 --> 43:52.424
[Larry] Yeah.

43:52.507 --> 43:53.883
[in normal voice] Okay.

43:54.009 --> 43:55.510
Can someone pass the ham?

43:58.596 --> 44:00.265
[dishes clanking]

44:00.932 --> 44:01.850
Who's next?

44:05.020 --> 44:06.354
[sniffing]

44:06.438 --> 44:08.523
Okay, I'll go next.
[clears throat]

44:09.190 --> 44:10.900
[sighs deeply]

44:11.026 --> 44:12.736
Uh, Immortus,

44:12.861 --> 44:16.781
I am grateful that
you were there for me
in my time of need.

44:16.865 --> 44:19.993
I needed to do a giant pish,

44:20.076 --> 44:23.038
and you provided a wipe

44:23.121 --> 44:25.874
-for me to freshen up my fufu.
-[Rita softly] Mm-mm.

44:25.957 --> 44:27.834
And for that, I thank you.

44:29.711 --> 44:32.213
Except that
this is Immortimas Day,

44:32.297 --> 44:34.049
and you couldn't
possibly know that, Rouge,

44:34.174 --> 44:37.510
because there
only is Immortimas Day.

44:37.594 --> 44:42.557
Except, Willie-Wanks-A-Lot,
this world isn't real.

44:42.682 --> 44:45.310
Now you should know
it was super easy
to figure that out

44:45.393 --> 44:47.479
because you didn't
even try to hide

44:47.562 --> 44:50.607
that this is
an alternate reality,

44:50.732 --> 44:52.567
or maybe you just suck at this.

44:52.692 --> 44:55.236
-[Isabel grunts]
-[Madame Rouge chokes]

44:58.031 --> 45:01.618
Don't you all agree Rouge
is the ultimate party pooper?

45:01.743 --> 45:03.244
[gasping]

45:04.496 --> 45:07.374
[in demonic voice]
Don't you agree?

45:07.457 --> 45:09.542
[all agreeing] Yes, uh-huh.

45:09.626 --> 45:10.794
Smelled that shit
from over here.

45:10.919 --> 45:12.295
-[Larry] Yeah.
-[Vic] Party pooper.

45:12.420 --> 45:14.673
[in normal voice]
Now, my question was,

45:16.257 --> 45:17.842
what are you grateful for?

45:19.469 --> 45:22.263
[straining and choking]

45:23.098 --> 45:25.183
Sing out, Louise!

45:25.266 --> 45:27.560
[straining and choking]

45:29.979 --> 45:31.439
I have something to say!

45:32.941 --> 45:34.901
Uh, because Immortus,

45:34.984 --> 45:38.238
I have so much
to thank you for. [chuckles]

45:38.321 --> 45:41.783
Lovely. [clears throat]
Proceed.

45:41.908 --> 45:46.788
We are all grateful for you,
because without you,

45:46.913 --> 45:50.041
we would not be the incredible
people at this table.

45:50.125 --> 45:53.837
I have to admit
you've been a role model to me.

45:53.962 --> 45:58.299
You've taught me what it means
to be... an icon and a hero.

46:00.135 --> 46:02.220
Thank you, Rita. [sighs]

46:02.303 --> 46:04.681
-Who's next--
-I'm not done.

46:04.806 --> 46:10.061
Your need for constant
attention and adulation
is inspiring.

46:10.145 --> 46:12.439
Your hunger for perfection...

46:12.522 --> 46:14.149
[chuckling] ...although
a hopeless endeavor,

46:14.274 --> 46:18.820
is almost as impressive
as your lack of self-awareness.

46:18.945 --> 46:22.198
And finally, and this is
what I do admire most,

46:22.323 --> 46:27.245
your ability to be
an even bigger narcissist
than I could ever be.

46:27.328 --> 46:30.540
You think you're all powerful?
You think you're all knowing?

46:30.665 --> 46:33.418
Well, I know you
because I was you.

46:33.501 --> 46:36.504
And I don't
want to be you anymore.

46:36.629 --> 46:39.841
It is a sad,
lonely, pathetic existence.

46:44.179 --> 46:45.638
[Larry sighs] Oh.

46:49.768 --> 46:50.643
[sighs]

46:50.727 --> 46:55.023
I see. And do you all agree?

46:55.106 --> 46:58.234
[emphatically] Absolutely not!

46:58.360 --> 47:00.028
Praise Immortus!

47:00.111 --> 47:03.698
[laughing] We all love you.

47:03.823 --> 47:06.326
-And Immortimas Day!
-[Isabel and Cliff chuckle]

47:06.409 --> 47:08.995
[sputtering]
That's not what Rita means.

47:09.079 --> 47:10.538
She's just tired.

47:10.622 --> 47:12.457
That's just...
It's the ham fumes.

47:12.540 --> 47:15.710
-You know how it is.
-Yeah. Yeah.

47:16.628 --> 47:18.630
Actually, I agree with Rita.

47:18.713 --> 47:21.716
-What the fuck?
-[Vic] Dude, let her speak.

47:21.841 --> 47:24.761
I'm not sure
this is what I want anymore.

47:26.554 --> 47:29.391
Immortimas is
just another prison.

47:29.516 --> 47:31.476
It's another lie.

47:31.559 --> 47:34.062
And I'm done lying to myself.

47:34.187 --> 47:38.900
I'm 100 years old,
for God's sake,
and I'm still hiding.

47:39.025 --> 47:42.487
I have never
lived out in the real world.

47:43.863 --> 47:46.032
I can't lock myself
away anymore.

47:47.283 --> 47:48.410
I need to go.

47:53.289 --> 47:54.499
Then I'll go with you.

47:55.208 --> 47:56.501
What?

47:56.584 --> 47:59.170
So, that's three votes
to leave Immortimas.

47:59.254 --> 48:03.258
No, no, no, no, no.
That... that's not
what she means.

48:03.383 --> 48:06.553
Dorothy loves Immortimas Day.

48:06.636 --> 48:10.140
And-- Who... who is this?

48:10.265 --> 48:11.975
[sighs in exasperation]

48:12.100 --> 48:16.938
I'm just saying that...
I thought I found
a new adventure here.

48:18.189 --> 48:19.524
A new experience.

48:20.608 --> 48:21.901
Clearly I was wrong.

48:23.528 --> 48:25.155
If I'm going to be
a hero in the real world,

48:25.280 --> 48:26.948
I need to see the real world.

48:27.073 --> 48:28.616
No, come on.

48:28.700 --> 48:32.787
Can't a... a human man
catch a break?

48:32.871 --> 48:38.126
[chuckling nervously]
I mean, she's not even with us.

48:38.209 --> 48:39.169
What is your name?

48:39.294 --> 48:40.795
I really wanted to stay here.

48:40.879 --> 48:42.672
It's about as perfect
as perfect can be.

48:42.797 --> 48:47.218
Finally, someone
saying the things
that we all are thinking.

48:47.302 --> 48:50.972
-But if I'm being honest
with myself...
-Fuck me.

48:51.097 --> 48:54.476
It's another story
being written for me.

48:54.559 --> 48:56.144
-You were right all along.
-[Larry sighs]

48:56.227 --> 48:58.313
I don't want to live
in a fake world either.

48:58.438 --> 48:59.689
How can I know
what I truly want,

48:59.814 --> 49:03.318
when people
keep rewriting my backstory?

49:03.401 --> 49:06.154
How can I trust my feelings
when I don't even
know who I am?

49:08.073 --> 49:09.949
I need to write
my own story for once.

49:10.867 --> 49:12.410
You wanna leave?

49:12.494 --> 49:14.996
But you said... [sighs]

49:15.121 --> 49:16.164
I don't want you to leave.

49:18.124 --> 49:20.085
He's not with us either.

49:20.168 --> 49:22.504
That's four votes.

49:25.215 --> 49:26.383
And I'm five.

49:28.510 --> 49:29.761
[plate clatters]

49:31.846 --> 49:34.974
So basically what we're trying
to say is fuck you

49:35.058 --> 49:36.518
and fuck Immortimas.

49:36.643 --> 49:38.603
-[table thuds]
-[gasping]

49:40.063 --> 49:42.565
[coughing and panting]

49:42.691 --> 49:43.983
[groaning softly]

49:45.485 --> 49:46.903
[sobbing]

49:49.572 --> 49:51.199
[sinister music playing]

49:54.035 --> 49:55.245
[sniffs]

49:55.370 --> 49:56.871
[growls in demonic voice]

49:57.706 --> 49:59.207
[clears throat]

49:59.290 --> 50:00.583
[grunts]

50:02.377 --> 50:04.129
[grumbling]

50:05.380 --> 50:06.756
[wailing in frustration]

50:06.881 --> 50:09.759
[screams in demonic voice]

50:10.510 --> 50:11.678
[grunts]

50:16.057 --> 50:17.517
[thunder rumbling]

50:18.601 --> 50:19.602
[in demonic voice] Move.

50:19.728 --> 50:21.479
[tense music playing]

50:23.732 --> 50:25.150
[thunder claps]

50:40.331 --> 50:44.919
♪ I fix all your problems
And what do you do? ♪

50:45.045 --> 50:47.756
♪ You find a way to break out ♪

50:47.881 --> 50:51.760
♪ And make it all about you ♪

50:56.765 --> 50:59.476
♪ Was it really so hard ♪

50:59.601 --> 51:06.274
♪ To give me
All your love and devotion ♪

51:06.399 --> 51:09.402
♪ I could have
Chosen the timeline ♪

51:09.486 --> 51:14.783
♪ That featured lotion ♪

51:14.908 --> 51:19.120
-♪ You're all doomed! ♪
-♪ Doomed! ♪

51:19.245 --> 51:23.333
♪ Sorry not sorry
To break the bad news ♪

51:23.458 --> 51:29.964
-♪ Doomed! Doomed! Doomed! ♪
-♪ Doomed! Doomed! Doomed! ♪

51:30.048 --> 51:32.384
♪ Doomed! Doomed! ♪

51:32.467 --> 51:36.763
♪ Aw, you think you've won?
Yeah, you think I'm done? ♪

51:36.846 --> 51:39.307
♪ Think again
The age of Immortus ♪

51:39.432 --> 51:41.810
♪ Has just begun ♪

51:42.686 --> 51:44.312
What are you gonna do, kill us?

51:45.230 --> 51:48.024
[laughs] I don't have to.

51:48.149 --> 51:53.363
♪ 'Cause you're all doomed ♪

51:53.488 --> 51:57.659
♪ Sorry not sorry
To break the bad news ♪

51:57.742 --> 52:01.830
-♪ Doomed! Doomed! ♪
-♪ Doomed! Doomed! ♪

52:01.913 --> 52:04.332
♪ You're about to blow
My dude ♪

52:04.457 --> 52:10.839
♪ You're all doomed ♪

52:10.964 --> 52:12.340
-[clicks fingers]
-[thunder claps]

52:12.424 --> 52:14.342
[song ends]

52:14.467 --> 52:15.593
[Rita gasps]

52:16.678 --> 52:18.596
[machinery whirring]

52:23.184 --> 52:24.102
[sighs]

52:24.185 --> 52:25.186
[paper flapping]

52:28.523 --> 52:29.733
[Rita sighs]

52:31.860 --> 52:33.862
Son of a bitch.
